				<h2>Are questions about installing OS X on PC on-topic</h2>
<p>...or do you have any suggestion, where I could ask such?</p>

<p>I would like to build an iOS application, for which I nead a real OS X-based machine or a service like Macincloud. However, <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/23682404/1469208">this answer</a> suggested, that I can just purchase an OS X and install it on my own PC, either as dual-boot secondary system or as virtual machine.</p>

<p>However, I'm such newbie (ignorant) to OS X and Apple topics, that until reaching out that answer, I even wasn't aware, that it is possible to purchase OS X without purchasing a hardware along with it. And the idea of installing it on PC sounds like a nightmare for me. And that is why I wanted to ask for a possible quick step-by-step guide or a link to an external source, where these matters are covered.</p>

<p>But... I think, that this could be an off-topic question and would like to confirm this before.</p>

